To adhere to SRP, responsibilities should be separated:

* `ReportGenerator`: Responsible for fetching and preparing the raw report data.
* `ReportFormatter`: Responsible for taking raw report data and formatting it (e.g., into a presentable HTML table or structured JSON).
* `PdfExporter`: Responsible for converting formatted report data into a PDF file.
* `CsvExporter`: Responsible for converting formatted report data into a CSV file.

```typescript
// TypeScript Interfaces/Classes
interface ReportData {
  // ... report data structure
}

interface FormattedReport {
  // ... formatted report structure
}

interface IReportGenerator {
  generateReport(criteria: any): ReportData;
}

interface IReportFormatter {
  format(data: ReportData): FormattedReport;
}

interface IReportExporter {
  export(formattedReport: FormattedReport): void;
}

class SalesReportGenerator implements IReportGenerator {
  generateReport(criteria: any): ReportData { 
    console.log('Generating sales report...');
    return { /* ... actual data */ }; 
  }
}

class TableReportFormatter implements IReportFormatter {
  format(data: ReportData): FormattedReport { 
    console.log('Formatting report as table...');
    return { /* ... formatted data */ }; 
  }
}

class PdfReportExporter implements IReportExporter {
  export(formattedReport: FormattedReport): void { 
    console.log('Exporting report to PDF...');
    // ... PDF generation logic 
  }
}

class CsvReportExporter implements IReportExporter {
  export(formattedReport: FormattedReport): void { 
    console.log('Exporting report to CSV...');
    // ... CSV generation logic 
  }
}
```
This design ensures that each class has a single reason to change. If PDF export logic changes, only `PdfExporter` is affected.

